2. Public broadcasts are not typically transmitted through cable connections.
3. Cable boxes are usually required to receive premium channels and pay-per-view content.
4. While some cable providers may offer free channels, these are often limited and not the same as public broadcasts.
5. Cable boxes require a subscription fee, which can be expensive over time.

